org.csiro.darjeeling.infuser.structure
Enum BaseType

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<BaseType>
      org.csiro.darjeeling.infuser.structure.BaseType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BaseType>
public enum BaseType
extends java.lang.Enum<BaseType>

Provides a mapping between Java types and the different base types used in Darjeeling. These can be either integer types such as Byte, Char, Boolean, Short, Int, and the currently unsupported Float, Long, and Double, or Reference.

The size of a BaseType is the number of bytes it takes to store a variable of that type, or -1 for references.

The TType property corresponds to the index given to a basetype in the Java VM spec.

Author:
Niels Brouwers

getNrIntegerSlots

public int getNrIntegerSlots()
Gets the number of slots on the integer stack that this type takes. Shorts, bytes, booleans and chars take up a single slot, integers and floats take two, and doubles and longs take four.

Returns:
the number of slots on the integer stack that this element takes

getNrReferenceSlots

max

public static BaseType max(BaseType a,
                           BaseType b)
Returns the 'largest' of the two types. The decision is made by size in bytes, so a Short is larger than a Byte, but smaller than an Int. Note that behavior is undefined for non-integer types.

Parameters:
a - a BaseType to compare
b - a BaseType to compare
Returns:
the largest of the two types or b in case of equal size

min

Returns the 'smallest' of the two types. The decision is made by size in bytes, so a Short is larger than a Byte, but smaller than an Int. Note that behavior is undefined for non-integer types.

Parameters:
a - a BaseType to compare
b - a BaseType to compare
Returns:
the smallest of the two types or b in case of equal size
